Ncell Logo
Ncell Axiata Limited is a mobile service provider from Nepal. It was founded in 2004 and launched its service commercially as “Mero Mobile” brand in September 2005. In March 2010, it was re-branded as “Ncell” by its parent company Telia Company. On 12 April 2016, Ncell became a part of Axiata Group Berhad when the group bought 100% of the shares of Reynolds Holdings, which then held 80% of Ncell shares.

item.title: Ncell
item.description: Ncell Axiata Limited is a mobile service provider from Nepal. It was founded in 2004 and launched its service commercially as “Mero Mobile” brand in September 2005. In March 2010, it was re-branded as “Ncell” by its parent company Telia Company. On 12 April 2016, Ncell became a part of Axiata Group Berhad when the group bought 100% of the shares of Reynolds Holdings, which then held 80% of Ncell shares.
